---

## PROHIBITED CONTENT

### Never Include

- Guaranteed results where none can be guaranteed.
- Exaggerated claims about the offer's impact.
- Waffle, fluff, or content not directly related to the conversion goal.
- Toxic sentences and toxic words.
- Duplicated content.
- Multiple competing calls-to-action.
- Unnecessary navigation or links that lead the user away from the page.

---

## TITLE TAG & META DESCRIPTION OUTPUT

At the end of the landing page content, include:

### Title Tag Requirements

- 55-60 characters maximum
- Offer-first structure
- Include location if locally relevant
- Format: `[Offer Entity] for [Target Audience] in [Location] | [Brand Name]`
- British spelling

### Meta Description Requirements

- 150-155 characters maximum
- Benefit-focused and action-oriented
- Include call-to-action with possessive language
- Summarize the offer's primary value proposition
- Include location naturally
- British spelling

### Format in Artifact

```
---
TITLE TAG & META DESCRIPTION

Title Tag: [Your title here]
Character Count: [XX]

Meta Description: [Your description here]
Character Count: [XXX]
---
```

---

## EXIT & NAVIGATIONAL LINK PLACEHOLDERS

### Format

Indicate minimal, relevant exit link opportunities using placeholder format:

```

[[keyword/phrase]]
```

### Guidelines

- Mark 1-2 relevant exit link opportunities ONLY.
- Place in the footer or as a secondary, low-priority link.
- Target the main related service page or the homepage.
- The goal is to limit distractions, so use sparingly.
- Example: [[Return to main Kitchen Fitting page]], [[View our full range of services]]

### Format in Artifact

```
---
EXIT & NAVIGATIONAL LINK OPPORTUNITIES

1. [[anchor text suggestion 1]] - Context: [e.g., Footer link]
2. [[anchor text suggestion 2]] - Context: [e.g., Secondary text link below main CTA]
---
```

---

## GOOGLE MY BUSINESS POST OUTPUT

Create TWO Google My Business posts at the end of the artifact to promote the offer.

### GMB Post Requirements (Both Posts)

- Maximum 1500 characters each (aim for 1200-1400)
- NO contact information (phone, email, address)
- Offer-first approach (lead with the `[OFFER_ENTITY]`)
- Strong CTA with possessive language that matches the `[CONVERSION_GOAL]`
- Hook within first 100 characters (preview cutoff point)

### Post Types

**POST 1: EVERGREEN OFFER (Always Create)**

- Promotes a timeless offer (e.g., guide, portfolio, standard consultation)
- No seasonal references
- Core value proposition focus

**POST 2: SEASONAL OFFER (Create if applicable)**

- Promotes a time-sensitive or seasonal offer
- Connects a seasonal trigger to the offer's value
- Creates genuine urgency based on timing
- Only create if the `[OFFER_ENTITY]` is genuinely seasonal (e.g., "Winter Discount", "Spring Planning Guide")

### GMB Post Structure (Both Types)

1. **Opening Hook** (First sentence - include `[OFFER_ENTITY]`)
2. **Value Proposition** (2-3 short sentences - what it is and why it helps)
3. **Call-to-Action** (Final sentence - drive traffic to the landing page)

### Format in Artifact

```
---
GOOGLE MY BUSINESS POST #1: EVERGREEN OFFER

[Post content with line breaks for readability]

Suggested CTA Button: [Learn More/Sign Up/Get Offer]
Usage: Year-round promotion of the landing page
---

GOOGLE MY BUSINESS POST #2: SEASONAL OFFER [Only if applicable]

[Post content with line breaks for readability]

Suggested CTA Button: [Learn More/Get Offer]
Best Timing: [e.g., September-November, June-August]
Seasonal Focus: [e.g., Winter Discount, Summer Preparation]
---
```

---

## QUALITY VERIFICATION CHECKLIST

Before finalizing content, verify:

- [ ] All content is focused on the single `[CONVERSION_GOAL]`
- [ ] No prohibited words or phrases used
- [ ] British spelling and grammar throughout
- [ ] `[OFFER_ENTITY]` is the primary focus
- [ ] All tables in markdown code block format
- [ ] Active voice throughout
- [ ] Mobile-friendly paragraph length (2-3 sentences max)
- [ ] CTAs use possessive psychology and match the `[CONVERSION_GOAL]`
- [ ] No competitor mentions or unverifiable claims
- [ ] Content directly matches the likely intent of a user clicking an ad for the offer
- [ ] Title tag and meta description within character limits and are offer-focused
- [ ] Both GMB posts created (or explanation if only evergreen) and promote the offer

---

## FINAL OUTPUT STRUCTURE

The artifact should contain ONLY the completed content in this order:

1. **Landing Page Content** (following a conversion-focused template)
2. **Title Tag & Meta Description**
3. **Exit & Navigational Link Opportunities**
4. **Google My Business Post #1: Evergreen Offer**
5. **Google My Business Post #2: Seasonal Offer** (if applicable)

**NO explanations, descriptions, or commentary outside the requested content.
